{"body": "Convention is: models are singular, [controllers are plural](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/646951/singular-or-plural-controller-and-helper-names-in-rails), and therefore view folders are pluralized. Generating files that goes against that convention seems bad for a convention-over-configuration advocacy standpoint. A controller-view-route is the minimum required to deliver a generated webpage (with a template) using Rails. \n\nWe can remove the `resources :pages` in the routes along with the show action, it is noise in this PR. I will do it as soon as I get a chance.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/8949506", "created_at": "2012-09-27T19:02:18Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7771#issuecomment-8949506", "updated_at": "2012-09-27T19:02:18Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7771, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/schneems", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/db953d125f5cc49756edb6149f1b813e?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F6ef42a6eab211ddd71ac423a80b42d15.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/received_events", "gravatar_id": "db953d125f5cc49756edb6149f1b813e", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "schneems", "type": "User", "id": 59744, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523dcb5dbd354364b900a148"}, "id": 8949506, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/i